CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 15, 1959, pg. A1, reads: "Filth and Stench Found in 3rd Ward - Living With Stench - Mrs.. Elmer Proctor, 1543 Clark St., shown with her five children, told a Courier reporter, 'We can't open our door because of stench and swarms of files' from the adjacent open garbage dump, where a city dumpster is placed, but not used properly, nor removed frequently. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Mrs. Elmer Proctor and her five children, posed at top of wooden steps of their home, with Dumpster and debris on adjacent lot, 1543 Clark Street, Hill District
